      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VINCENT BALE (1) boasts a consistent overall record including 26 wins from 77 starts, the latest hitting the minor money when third (29.48) over 515m at Sandown. Form at the trip sound including five wins. Rates strongly and will go close from the inside draw. LAURISTON GIRL (3) pinged the lids from the low draw and led until late to place (23.02) at this track in a Free For All over 410m. The form out of her last race has been franked. Expected to be in the finish again. PAW DROGO (2) goes very well this course and distance starting eight times for three wins and four minors. Was out of the placings last time (22.46) at Ballarat in a Grade 4, finishing seventh and beaten 9 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. PAW OLYMPUS (7) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
